Note:
This file handles loop auto-vectorization for MIR.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process natural-loop detection over the canonical CFG (back edges via
  the dominance tree; predecessor/successor lists hold BLOCK IDS)
- Handle induction-variable recognition, affine address decomposition,
  and consecutive-access classification
- Manage loop-carried dependence legality and profitability gating
- Process scalar-to-vector widening into canonical MIRVectorOp records

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Vectorization enables SIMD instructions for massive performance gains
- The legality gates are the soundness boundary between parallel-lane
  execution and silently wrong vector code
- Auto-vectorization lets scalar Runa loops use vector hardware

Reconciled to the canonical MIR contract (task #471, after the #432 waves).
The honest vectorization domain in THIS IR:

  TRANSFORM DOMAIN (every condition compiler-proven, else REJECT):
  - a natural single-latch loop whose body is straight-line (the only
    branch is the loop exit test),
  - one basic induction variable: header PHI with a CONST init and a
    latch update ADD(iv, CONST 1) - and no other header phi (a second
    header phi is a loop-carried scalar cycle the lanewise model cannot
    honor),
  - a loop test LT/LE against a CONST bound on the IV phi (header-test
    shape) or on the updated IV (latch-test shape), continuing on the
    TRUE edge,
  - a compile-time trip count that is >= the vector factor and an exact
    multiple of it (so no remainder epilogue and no runtime guard are
    needed - the widened loop is exactly equivalent),
  - every data-side body instruction widenable to a vector opcode the
    LIR builder actually lowers (lower_vector_op arms): ADD/SUB/MUL/DIV
    (20002-20005 -> 20600-20603), AND/OR/XOR (20010-20012 ->
    20620-20622), LOAD 20200 -> VECTOR_LOAD 20610, STORE 20201 ->
    VECTOR_STORE 20611,
  - every widened memory access affine in the IV with byte stride
    exactly equal to its element size (consecutive lanes),
  - dependence freedom: same-base pairs must be provably intra-iteration
    or provably never-coinciding; different-base pairs are accepted only
    when both bases are distinct ALLOCA results (disjoint stack objects),
  - widened values produced and consumed entirely inside the widen set
    (a scalar consumer of a vector value, or a scalar/IV-derived data
    operand of a vector op, is rejected: the lowerable opcode set has no
    broadcast or lane-iota form - MIR_VECTOR_BROADCAST 20615 exists in
    the band but lower_vector_op has no arm for it, which is reported as
    a backend gap, not silently emitted).

  The widening REPLACES each scalar instruction with a FRESH canonical
  MIRVectorOp record (record-size discipline: a 104-byte binary op or a
  112-byte load/store cannot legally become a 128-byte vector record in
  place), keeps the SAME result value id (every existing use stays
  valid; register_value_definition re-points the definition), bumps the
  IV step to a freshly materialized CONST(VF) rewired through
  MIRNodes.set_mir_node_used_value, and leaves the CFG topology
  untouched (no prologue/epilogue blocks are needed inside the proven
  domain, so dominance stays valid).

Integer-keyed maps use collections/ordered_map because the dictionary
primitive string-hashes its keys (integer keys crash at runtime - Wave 3
finding). Set elements are raw integers (Wave 5a finding). All new SSA
ids come from MIR.allocate_value_id + register_value_definition, and
integers are displayed through StringUtils.integer_to_string.
:End Note

Note: ============================================================================
Note: IMPORTS
Note: ============================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir.runa" as MIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir_nodes.runa" as MIRNodes
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/cfg.runa" as CFG
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/dominance.runa" as Dominance
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/ordered_map.runa" as OMap
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/set.runa" as Set
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPE DEFINITIONS
Note: ============================================================================

Type called "VectorizationContext":
    @Reasoning
    Per-function state for the vectorization pass.

    **MEMORY LAYOUT** (96 bytes):
    ```
    Offset 0:  function_ptr (Integer - MIRFunction pointer; value-id
               allocation and definition registration thread through it)
    Offset 8:  cfg (Integer - MIRCFG pointer, function offset 8)
    Offset 16: dom_info (Integer - dominance info from
               Dominance.compute_dominance_tree; owned, freed on destroy)
    Offset 24: def_map (Integer - OMap value_id -> defining instruction;
               one O(I) CFG scan, the licm/devirt local-def-map precedent:
               SSA never materializes MIRValue use-lists)
    Offset 32: loops (Integer - List of VectorLoopInfo records; owned)
    Offset 40: vectorized_loops (Integer - loops successfully widened)
    Offset 48: rejected_loops (Integer - loops rejected by any gate)
    Offset 56: instructions_vectorized (Integer - scalar records replaced)
    Offset 64: profitability_threshold (Integer - minimum fixed-point
               speedup ratio scaled by 100; default 120 = 1.2x)
    Offset 72: target_vector_width (Integer - lanes per vector; default 4,
               the SSE/NEON int64x... baseline the LIR vector lowering
               assumes; the target-selection driver may raise it)
    Offset 80: vector_width_used (Integer - factor of the last applied
               widening, 0 when none)
    Offset 88: reserved (Integer - keeps the record 8-slot aligned)
    ```
    @End Reasoning

    function_ptr as Integer
    cfg as Integer
    dom_info as Integer
    def_map as Integer
    loops as Integer
    vectorized_loops as Integer
    rejected_loops as Integer
    instructions_vectorized as Integer
    profitability_threshold as Integer
    target_vector_width as Integer
    vector_width_used as Integer
    reserved as Integer
End Type

Type called "VectorLoopInfo":
    @Reasoning
    One analyzed natural loop.

    **MEMORY LAYOUT** (136 bytes):
    ```
    Offset 0:   header_id (Integer - loop header block id)
    Offset 8:   preheader_id (Integer - the single out-of-loop header
                predecessor; -1 when the shape is unsupported)
    Offset 16:  latch_id (Integer - back-edge source block id)
    Offset 24:  body_blocks (Integer - Set of body block ids, raw ints)
    Offset 32:  exit_block_id (Integer - the single out-of-loop successor;
                -1 until resolved)
    Offset 40:  iv_phi (Integer - the IV header phi instruction)
    Offset 48:  iv_value_id (Integer - the phi's SSA result id)
    Offset 56:  iv_update_inst (Integer - the latch ADD(iv, CONST stride))
    Offset 64:  iv_init (Integer - compile-time IV start value)
    Offset 72:  iv_bound (Integer - compile-time loop bound)
    Offset 80:  trip_count (Integer - compile-time trips; -1 unknown)
    Offset 88:  vectorizable (Integer - 1 after all gates pass)
    Offset 96:  rejection_reason (Integer - reason code, 0 none; see
                vect_reject for the code legend)
    Offset 104: vector_factor (Integer - lanes used by the transform)
    Offset 112: accesses (Integer - List of MemoryAccess records; owned)
    Offset 120: deps (Integer - List of DependencyInfo records; owned)
    Offset 128: exit_test_block_id (Integer - block holding the exit
                branch; -1 until resolved)
    ```
    @End Reasoning

    header_id as Integer
    preheader_id as Integer
    latch_id as Integer
    body_blocks as Integer
    exit_block_id as Integer
    iv_phi as Integer
    iv_value_id as Integer
    iv_update_inst as Integer
    iv_init as Integer
    iv_bound as Integer
    trip_count as Integer
    vectorizable as Integer
    rejection_reason as Integer
    vector_factor as Integer
    accesses as Integer
    deps as Integer
    exit_test_block_id as Integer
End Type

Type called "MemoryAccess":
    @Reasoning
    One load or store inside the loop body, decomposed into affine form
    address = base + delta * iteration + const_offset (all in bytes).

    **MEMORY LAYOUT** (72 bytes):
    ```
    Offset 0:  instruction_ptr (Integer - the MIR load/store record)
    Offset 8:  is_store (Integer - 1 store, 0 load)
    Offset 16: address_value (Integer - SSA value id of the address)
    Offset 24: base_value (Integer - SSA value id of the loop-invariant
               base leaf; 0 when the address is pure constant)
    Offset 32: delta_bytes (Integer - address change per iteration)
    Offset 40: const_offset (Integer - constant byte offset, including
               the record's own ext offset field)
    Offset 48: element_size (Integer - access width in bytes)
    Offset 56: decomposed (Integer - 1 when the affine decomposition
               succeeded; 0 forces rejection of the loop)
    Offset 64: is_consecutive (Integer - delta_bytes == element_size)
    ```
    @End Reasoning

    instruction_ptr as Integer
    is_store as Integer
    address_value as Integer
    base_value as Integer
    delta_bytes as Integer
    const_offset as Integer
    element_size as Integer
    decomposed as Integer
    is_consecutive as Integer
End Type

Type called "DependencyInfo":
    @Reasoning
    One analyzed access pair that shares (or may share) memory.

    **MEMORY LAYOUT** (48 bytes):
    ```
    Offset 0:  source_access (Integer - MemoryAccess, earlier in program)
    Offset 8:  target_access (Integer - MemoryAccess, later in program)
    Offset 16: dependency_type (Integer - 1 RAW, 2 WAR, 3 WAW)
    Offset 24: distance (Integer - iteration distance when exact;
               meaningful only when is_exact is 1)
    Offset 32: is_exact (Integer - 1 when the distance is proven)
    Offset 40: blocks_vectorization (Integer - 1 when this pair forced
               rejection)
    ```
    @End Reasoning

    source_access as Integer
    target_access as Integer
    dependency_type as Integer
    distance as Integer
    is_exact as Integer
    blocks_vectorization as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DEFINITION MAP
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Pass-local definition map: SSA value id -> defining instruction pointer
(licm/devirt precedent). One O(I) scan; a value id ABSENT from the map is
defined outside every block (parameter / import), which the analyses
treat as a loop-invariant opaque leaf.
@End Reasoning

Process called "vect_build_def_map" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let def_map be proc omap_create from OMap
    If cfg_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return def_map
    End If

    Let blocks be proc get_mir_cfg_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    If blocks is equal to 0:
        Return def_map
    End If

    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let b_idx be 0
    While b_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be proc get from List with blocks, b_idx
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block_ptr
            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
                Let i_idx be 0
                While i_idx is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst_ptr be proc get from List with instructions, i_idx
                    If inst_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        Let value_id be proc get_mir_node_value_id from MIR with inst_ptr
                        If value_id is not equal to 0:
                            proc omap_set from OMap with def_map, value_id, inst_ptr
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set i_idx to i_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        Set b_idx to b_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return def_map
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONTEXT MANAGEMENT
Note: ============================================================================

@Implementation
Creates the per-function VectorizationContext: derives the CFG from the
function (canonical offset 8 via MIR.get_mir_function_cfg), computes the
dominance tree eagerly (back-edge detection needs it immediately), and
builds the local definition map. Returns 0 when the function, its CFG,
or the dominance computation is unavailable.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_vectorization_context" that takes function_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If function_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cfg_ptr be proc get_mir_function_cfg from MIR with function_ptr
    If cfg_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dom_info be proc compute_dominance_tree from Dominance with cfg_ptr
    If dom_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let context_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 96
    If context_ptr is equal to 0:
        proc destroy_dominance_info from Dominance with dom_info
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 0, function_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8, cfg_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 16, dom_info

    Let def_map be proc vect_build_def_map with cfg_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 24, def_map

    Let loops be proc create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 32, loops

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 56, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 64, 120
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 72, 4
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 80, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 88, 0

    Return context_ptr
End Process

@Implementation
Destroys the context bottom-up: per-loop accesses (records then List),
per-loop deps, per-loop body Set, the loop records, the loops List, the
definition map, the dominance info, then the context allocation itself.
Every owning pointer is null-checked so a partially constructed context
tears down safely.
@End Implementation

Process called "destroy_vectorization_context" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If context_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let loops be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 32
    If loops is not equal to 0:
        Let loop_count be proc length from List with loops
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than loop_count:
            Let loop_info be proc get from List with loops, i
            If loop_info is not equal to 0:
                Let body_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 24
                If body_set is not equal to 0:
                    proc destroy from Set with body_set
                End If

                Let accesses be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 112
                If accesses is not equal to 0:
                    Let acc_count be proc length from List with accesses
                    Let j be 0
                    While j is less than acc_count:
                        Let acc be proc get from List with accesses, j
                        If acc is not equal to 0:
                            proc deallocate from Layout with acc
                        End If
                        Set j to j plus 1
                    End While
                    proc destroy from List with accesses
                End If

                Let deps be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 120
                If deps is not equal to 0:
                    Let dep_count be proc length from List with deps
                    Let k be 0
                    While k is less than dep_count:
                        Let dep be proc get from List with deps, k
                        If dep is not equal to 0:
                            proc deallocate from Layout with dep
                        End If
                        Set k to k plus 1
                    End While
                    proc destroy from List with deps
                End If

                proc deallocate from Layout with loop_info
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc destroy from List with loops
    End If

    Let def_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 24
    If def_map is not equal to 0:
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with def_map
    End If

    Let dom_info be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 16
    If dom_info is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy_dominance_info from Dominance with dom_info
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with context_ptr
    Return 1
End Process

@Implementation
Prints pass statistics. Integers are rendered through
StringUtils.integer_to_string because Display on a raw integer joined
into a string crashes at runtime (diagnostics finding).
@End Implementation

Process called "print_vectorization_stats" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If context_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Display "========== Vectorization Statistics =========="

    Let vectorized be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 40
    Let vectorized_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with vectorized
    Display "Loops vectorized: " joined with vectorized_str

    Let rejected be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 48
    Let rejected_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with rejected
    Display "Loops rejected: " joined with rejected_str

    Let widened be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 56
    Let widened_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with widened
    Display "Instructions vectorized: " joined with widened_str

    Let width_used be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 80
    Let width_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with width_used
    Display "Vector width used: " joined with width_str

    Display "=============================================="
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Centralized rejection: stamps the loop non-vectorizable with a reason
code, bumps the context's rejected counter exactly once per loop, and
reports the human-readable reason. Reason legend:
 1 no induction variable          2 non-unit stride / non-consecutive
 3 multiple latches               4 unsupported control flow
 5 non-widenable instruction      6 loop-carried data dependence
 7 unprovable aliasing            8 trip count not statically known
 9 trip count below / not a multiple of the vector factor
 10 not profitable                11 scalar-vector operand mixing
 12 multiple header phis          13 preheader shape unsupported
 14 unsupported memory access     15 not an innermost loop
@End Reasoning

Process called "vect_reject" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, reason as Integer returns Integer:
    If loop_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Bump the rejected counter only on the first rejection of this loop
    Let prior be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 96
    If prior is equal to 0:
        Let rejected be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 48
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 48, rejected plus 1
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 88, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 96, reason

    If reason is equal to 1:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - no induction variable"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 2:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - non-unit stride or non-consecutive access"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 3:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - multiple latches"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 4:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - unsupported control flow"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 5:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - non-widenable instruction in body"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 6:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - loop-carried data dependence"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 7:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - unprovable aliasing"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 8:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - trip count not statically known"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 9:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - trip count below or not a multiple of the vector factor"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 10:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - not profitable"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 11:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - scalar-vector operand mixing"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 12:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - multiple header phis"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 13:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - preheader shape unsupported"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 14:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - unsupported memory access shape"
    End If
    If reason is equal to 15:
        Display "vectorization: rejected - not an innermost loop"
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NATURAL LOOP DETECTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Classical back-edge detection: an edge latch -> header where the header
dominates the latch (Dominance.dominates on BLOCK IDS - the canonical
pred/succ lists hold ids, never pointers). Each back edge yields one
VectorLoopInfo; a second back edge into the SAME header is a multi-latch
loop, which the single-latch widening model rejects (reason 3) rather
than mis-merging.

The successor lists returned by MIR.get_block_successors are the LIVE
CFG id lists - they are read in place and never destroyed.
@End Reasoning

Process called "detect_natural_loops" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If context_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8
    Let dom_info be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 16
    Let loops be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 32

    Let blocks be proc get_mir_cfg_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    If blocks is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: header_id -> loop_info, for multi-latch detection
    Let header_map be proc omap_create from OMap

    Let loops_found be 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be proc get from List with blocks, i
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let block_id be proc get_mir_basic_block_id from CFG with block_ptr
            Let successors be proc get_block_successors from MIR with block_ptr
            If successors is not equal to 0:
                Let succ_count be proc length from List with successors
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than succ_count:
                    Let succ_id be proc get from List with successors, j
                    Let is_back_edge be proc dominates from Dominance with dom_info, succ_id, block_id
                    If is_back_edge is equal to 1:
                        Let existing be proc omap_get from OMap with header_map, succ_id plus 1
                        If existing is not equal to 0:
                            Note: Second latch into the same header
                            proc vect_reject with context_ptr, existing, 3
                        Otherwise:
                            Let loop_info be proc create_loop_info_from_back_edge with context_ptr, block_id, succ_id
                            If loop_info is not equal to 0:
                                proc append from List with loops, loop_info
                                proc omap_set from OMap with header_map, succ_id plus 1, loop_info
                                Set loops_found to loops_found plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc omap_destroy from OMap with header_map
    Return loops_found
End Process

@Reasoning
Builds the loop's topological skeleton from one confirmed back edge:
- body via the standard reverse-reachability worklist from the latch
  (walk predecessor IDS, stop at the header; the header dominates every
  body block by the back-edge property, so the walk cannot escape),
- the unique preheader: the header must have exactly two predecessors,
  the latch (inside) and one outside block; any other shape gets
  preheader_id -1 and is rejected by the IV gate (reason 13),
- the unique exit edge: exactly one (body block -> outside block) edge;
  its source is the exit-test block. Zero or multiple exit edges set
  the -1 sentinels and the trip-count gate rejects (reason 4).
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_loop_info_from_back_edge" that takes context_ptr as Integer, latch_id as Integer, header_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8

    Let loop_info be proc allocate from Layout with 136
    If loop_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 0, header_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 16, latch_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 56, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 64, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 72, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 80, 0 minus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 88, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 96, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 104, 0

    Let accesses be proc create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 112, accesses
    Let deps be proc create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 120, deps

    Note: ---- Body: reverse reachability from the latch, stopping at the header
    Let body_set be proc create from Set
    proc add from Set with body_set, header_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 24, body_set

    Let worklist be proc create from List
    proc append from List with worklist, latch_id
    While proc length from List with worklist is greater than 0:
        Let wl_len be proc length from List with worklist
        Let current_id be proc get from List with worklist, wl_len minus 1
        proc remove_at from List with worklist, wl_len minus 1

        Let already be proc contains from Set with body_set, current_id
        If already is equal to 0:
            proc add from Set with body_set, current_id
            Let current_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, current_id
            If current_block is not equal to 0:
                Let preds be proc get_block_predecessors from MIR with current_block
                If preds is not equal to 0:
                    Let pred_count be proc length from List with preds
                    Let p be 0
                    While p is less than pred_count:
                        Let pred_id be proc get from List with preds, p
                        proc append from List with worklist, pred_id
                        Set p to p plus 1
                    End While
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    proc destroy from List with worklist

    Note: ---- Preheader: the single out-of-loop header predecessor
    Let preheader_id be 0 minus 1
    Let header_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, header_id
    If header_block is not equal to 0:
        Let header_preds be proc get_block_predecessors from MIR with header_block
        If header_preds is not equal to 0:
            Let hp_count be proc length from List with header_preds
            If hp_count is equal to 2:
                Let hp0 be proc get from List with header_preds, 0
                Let hp1 be proc get from List with header_preds, 1
                Let hp0_in be proc contains from Set with body_set, hp0
                Let hp1_in be proc contains from Set with body_set, hp1
                If hp0_in is equal to 0:
                    If hp1_in is equal to 1:
                        Set preheader_id to hp0
                    End If
                End If
                If hp1_in is equal to 0:
                    If hp0_in is equal to 1:
                        Set preheader_id to hp1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 8, preheader_id

    Note: ---- Exit edge: exactly one (body block -> outside) edge
    Let exit_block_id be 0 minus 1
    Let exit_test_block_id be 0 minus 1
    Let exit_edge_count be 0
    Let body_list be proc to_list from Set with body_set
    Let body_count be proc length from List with body_list
    Let b be 0
    While b is less than body_count:
        Let body_id be proc get from List with body_list, b
        Let body_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, body_id
        If body_block is not equal to 0:
            Let succs be proc get_block_successors from MIR with body_block
            If succs is not equal to 0:
                Let s_count be proc length from List with succs
                Let s be 0
                While s is less than s_count:
                    Let s_id be proc get from List with succs, s
                    Let s_in be proc contains from Set with body_set, s_id
                    If s_in is equal to 0:
                        Set exit_edge_count to exit_edge_count plus 1
                        Set exit_block_id to s_id
                        Set exit_test_block_id to body_id
                    End If
                    Set s to s plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        Set b to b plus 1
    End While
    proc destroy from List with body_list

    If exit_edge_count is not equal to 1:
        Set exit_block_id to 0 minus 1
        Set exit_test_block_id to 0 minus 1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 32, exit_block_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 128, exit_test_block_id

    Return loop_info
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INDUCTION VARIABLE AND TRIP COUNT ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Resolves a value id to its defining CONST's integer payload. Returns the
constant through the out parameter convention: the return value is 1 when
the value is a compile-time integer CONST (opcode 20001, non-string), 0
otherwise; the payload is written into out_ptr offset 0.
@End Reasoning

Process called "vect_constant_value" that takes context_ptr as Integer, value_id as Integer, out_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let def_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 24
    Let def_inst be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, value_id
    If def_inst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with def_inst
    If opcode is not equal to 20001:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: MIRConst is_string lives at ext offset 96 (Part 1.1) - string
    Note: constants carry a pointer payload, not an arithmetic value.
    Let is_string be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with def_inst, 96
    If is_string is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let value be proc get_const_value from MIRNodes with def_inst
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with out_ptr, 0, value
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Basic-induction-variable recognition on the canonical phi contract:
- the header must contain EXACTLY ONE phi (opcode 20300, canonical
  residence in the instruction list). A second header phi is a
  loop-carried scalar cycle (an accumulator/reduction); the lanewise
  widening model cannot honor it, so the loop is rejected (reason 12).
- the phi must have exactly two incomings (flat pair List, block at 2N,
  value at 2N+1, read through the MIRNodes accessors): one from a block
  inside the body (the latch update) and one from outside (the init).
- the update must be ADD(phi_result, CONST stride) in either operand
  order, with stride exactly 1 (reason 2 otherwise) - unit step is what
  makes "lane k = iteration i+k" line up with consecutive memory lanes.
- the init incoming must resolve to an integer CONST (reason 8
  otherwise; the divisibility proof needs the compile-time start).
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_induction_variable" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8
    Let def_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 24
    Let header_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 0
    Let body_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 24

    Let header_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, header_id
    If header_block is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Exactly one header phi
    Let iv_phi be 0
    Let phi_count be 0
    Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with header_block
    If instructions is not equal to 0:
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, i
            If inst is not equal to 0:
                Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst
                If opcode is equal to 20300:
                    Set phi_count to phi_count plus 1
                    Set iv_phi to inst
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    If phi_count is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 1
        Return 0
    End If
    If phi_count is greater than 1:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 12
        Return 0
    End If

    Let incoming_count be proc get_phi_incoming_count from MIRNodes with iv_phi
    If incoming_count is not equal to 2:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block0 be proc get_phi_incoming_block from MIRNodes with iv_phi, 0
    Let value0 be proc get_phi_incoming_value from MIRNodes with iv_phi, 0
    Let block1 be proc get_phi_incoming_block from MIRNodes with iv_phi, 1
    Let value1 be proc get_phi_incoming_value from MIRNodes with iv_phi, 1

    Let block0_in be proc contains from Set with body_set, block0
    Let block1_in be proc contains from Set with body_set, block1

    Let init_value be 0
    Let update_value be 0
    If block0_in is equal to 1:
        If block1_in is equal to 0:
            Set update_value to value0
            Set init_value to value1
        End If
    End If
    If block1_in is equal to 1:
        If block0_in is equal to 0:
            Set update_value to value1
            Set init_value to value0
        End If
    End If
    If update_value is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Preheader shape must have resolved (single outside pred)
    Let preheader_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 8
    If preheader_id is less than 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 13
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Update: ADD(phi, CONST 1)
    Let phi_result be proc get_mir_node_value_id from MIR with iv_phi
    Let update_inst be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, update_value
    If update_inst is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 1
        Return 0
    End If
    Let update_opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with update_inst
    If update_opcode is not equal to 20002:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let left be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with update_inst, 1
    Let right be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with update_inst, 2
    Let stride_value_id be 0
    If left is equal to phi_result:
        Set stride_value_id to right
    End If
    If right is equal to phi_result:
        If stride_value_id is equal to 0:
            Set stride_value_id to left
        End If
    End If
    If stride_value_id is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let scratch be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    Let stride_is_const be proc vect_constant_value with context_ptr, stride_value_id, scratch
    If stride_is_const is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with scratch
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 1
        Return 0
    End If
    Let stride be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scratch, 0
    If stride is not equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with scratch
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 2
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Init must be a compile-time constant
    Let init_is_const be proc vect_constant_value with context_ptr, init_value, scratch
    If init_is_const is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with scratch
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 8
        Return 0
    End If
    Let init be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scratch, 0
    proc deallocate from Layout with scratch

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 40, iv_phi
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 48, phi_result
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 56, update_inst
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 64, init
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Trip-count derivation from the single exit test. Supported shapes (the
two latch-test forms the lowering produces; everything else is reason 8):

  cond = LT(x, CONST N)  or  cond = LE(x, CONST N)
  BRANCH(cond, in_loop_target, exit_target)   - continue on TRUE

with x either the IV PHI result (header-test "while" shape) or the
UPDATED IV (latch-test "do-while" shape). For stride 1 the closed forms
coincide for both shapes once the trip count is at least 1 (the
divisibility gate enforces trips >= VF >= 2, which covers the do-while
at-least-once subtlety):

  LT: trips = N - init        LE: trips = N - init + 1

A branch whose FALSE side stays in the loop (continue-on-false) is
rejected rather than negated: the lowering does not produce that shape,
and accepting it untested would be dishonest coverage.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_trip_count" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8
    Let def_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 24
    Let body_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 24
    Let exit_test_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 128

    If exit_test_id is less than 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 4
        Return 0
    End If

    Let test_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, exit_test_id
    If test_block is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 4
        Return 0
    End If

    Let terminator be proc get_block_terminator from CFG with test_block
    If terminator is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 4
        Return 0
    End If
    Let term_opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with terminator
    If term_opcode is not equal to 20301:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 4
        Return 0
    End If

    Let true_block be proc get_mir_branch_true_block from MIRNodes with terminator
    Let false_block be proc get_mir_branch_false_block from MIRNodes with terminator
    Let true_in be proc contains from Set with body_set, true_block
    Let false_in be proc contains from Set with body_set, false_block

    Note: Continue on TRUE, exit on FALSE - the only supported polarity
    If true_in is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 8
        Return 0
    End If
    If false_in is equal to 1:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 4
        Return 0
    End If

    Let condition be proc get_branch_condition from MIRNodes with terminator
    Let cond_inst be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, condition
    If cond_inst is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 8
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cond_opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with cond_inst
    Let is_lt be 0
    Let is_le be 0
    If cond_opcode is equal to 20102:
        Set is_lt to 1
    End If
    If cond_opcode is equal to 20103:
        Set is_le to 1
    End If
    If is_lt is equal to 0:
        If is_le is equal to 0:
            proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 8
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Let iv_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 48
    Let update_inst be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 56
    Let updated_value be proc get_mir_node_value_id from MIR with update_inst

    Let cmp_left be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with cond_inst, 1
    Let cmp_right be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with cond_inst, 2

    Let left_is_iv be 0
    If cmp_left is equal to iv_value:
        Set left_is_iv to 1
    End If
    If cmp_left is equal to updated_value:
        Set left_is_iv to 1
    End If
    If left_is_iv is equal to 0:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 8
        Return 0
    End If

    Let scratch be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    Let bound_is_const be proc vect_constant_value with context_ptr, cmp_right, scratch
    If bound_is_const is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with scratch
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 8
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bound be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scratch, 0
    proc deallocate from Layout with scratch

    Let init be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 64
    Let trips be bound minus init
    If is_le is equal to 1:
        Set trips to trips plus 1
    End If
    If trips is less than 1:
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 9
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 72, bound
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 80, trips
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AFFINE ADDRESS DECOMPOSITION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Decomposes an SSA value used in address arithmetic into affine form

    value(iteration) = delta * iteration + const + base

where base is at most ONE loop-invariant opaque leaf (a parameter, an
ALLOCA result, or any value defined outside the body). The result is
written into a 32-byte accumulator: ok@0, delta@8, const@16, base@24.

Recognized forms over the def chain (depth-bounded; cycles are
impossible below the IV phi because every other phi fails the match):
  IV phi result      -> (delta 1, const 0)        [stride proven 1]
  integer CONST c    -> (delta 0, const c)
  out-of-body def    -> (delta 0, const 0, base v) [invariant leaf]
  no def (parameter) -> (delta 0, const 0, base v) [invariant leaf]
  ADD(a, b)          -> componentwise sum; at most one side carries base
  SUB(a, b)          -> componentwise difference; base only on the left
  MUL(a, CONST c) / MUL(CONST c, a)
                     -> scaled; fails when the scaled side carries base
  anything else      -> decomposition failure (ok 0)

Failure never wrongly classifies: the caller treats ok 0 as
non-consecutive, which the legality gate turns into rejection.
@End Reasoning

Process called "vect_decompose_value" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, value_id as Integer, acc as Integer, depth as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 24, 0

    If value_id is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If depth is greater than 64:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: The IV itself: one step per iteration (stride proven 1)
    Let iv_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 48
    If value_id is equal to iv_value:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 0, 1
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 8, 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Let def_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 24
    Let def_inst be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, value_id
    If def_inst is equal to 0:
        Note: Parameter / imported value: loop-invariant opaque leaf
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 0, 1
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 24, value_id
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Defined outside the body: loop-invariant leaf as well
    Let body_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 24
    Let def_block be proc get_mir_node_parent_block from MIR with def_inst
    Let def_block_id be 0 minus 1
    If def_block is not equal to 0:
        Set def_block_id to proc get_mir_basic_block_id from CFG with def_block
    End If
    Let def_in_body be proc contains from Set with body_set, def_block_id
    If def_in_body is equal to 0:
        Let def_opcode_out be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with def_inst
        If def_opcode_out is equal to 20001:
            Note: Out-of-body integer constants fold into the const slot
            Let is_string_out be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with def_inst, 96
            If is_string_out is equal to 0:
                Let const_payload be proc get_const_value from MIRNodes with def_inst
                proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 0, 1
                proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 16, const_payload
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 0, 1
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 24, value_id
        Return 1
    End If

    Let def_opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with def_inst

    If def_opcode is equal to 20001:
        Let is_string be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with def_inst, 96
        If is_string is not equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let const_value be proc get_const_value from MIRNodes with def_inst
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 0, 1
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 16, const_value
        Return 1
    End If

    If def_opcode is equal to 20002:
        Let add_left be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with def_inst, 1
        Let add_right be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with def_inst, 2
        Let acc_l be proc allocate from Layout with 32
        Let acc_r be proc allocate from Layout with 32
        Let ok_l be proc vect_decompose_value with context_ptr, loop_info, add_left, acc_l, depth plus 1
        Let ok_r be proc vect_decompose_value with context_ptr, loop_info, add_right, acc_r, depth plus 1
        Let result be 0
        If ok_l is equal to 1:
            If ok_r is equal to 1:
                Let base_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with acc_l, 24
                Let base_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with acc_r, 24
                Let base_count be 0
                If base_l is not equal to 0:
                    Set base_count to base_count plus 1
                End If
                If base_r is not equal to 0:
                    Set base_count to base_count plus 1
                End If
                If base_count is less than 2:
                    Let delta_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with acc_l, 8
                    Let delta_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with acc_r, 8
                    Let const_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with acc_l, 16
                    Let const_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with acc_r, 16
                    Let base_sum be base_l
                    If base_r is not equal to 0:
                        Set base_sum to base_r
                    End If
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 0, 1
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 8, delta_l plus delta_r
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 16, const_l plus const_r
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 24, base_sum
                    Set result to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with acc_l
        proc deallocate from Layout with acc_r
        Return result
    End If

    If def_opcode is equal to 20003:
        Let sub_left be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with def_inst, 1
        Let sub_right be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with def_inst, 2
        Let sacc_l be proc allocate from Layout with 32
        Let sacc_r be proc allocate from Layout with 32
        Let sok_l be proc vect_decompose_value with context_ptr, loop_info, sub_left, sacc_l, depth plus 1
        Let sok_r be proc vect_decompose_value with context_ptr, loop_info, sub_right, sacc_r, depth plus 1
        Let sresult be 0
        If sok_l is equal to 1:
            If sok_r is equal to 1:
                Let sbase_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with sacc_r, 24
                If sbase_r is equal to 0:
                    Let sdelta_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with sacc_l, 8
                    Let sdelta_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with sacc_r, 8
                    Let sconst_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with sacc_l, 16
                    Let sconst_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with sacc_r, 16
                    Let sbase_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with sacc_l, 24
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 0, 1
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 8, sdelta_l minus sdelta_r
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 16, sconst_l minus sconst_r
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 24, sbase_l
                    Set sresult to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with sacc_l
        proc deallocate from Layout with sacc_r
        Return sresult
    End If

    If def_opcode is equal to 20004:
        Let mul_left be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with def_inst, 1
        Let mul_right be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with def_inst, 2
        Let macc_l be proc allocate from Layout with 32
        Let macc_r be proc allocate from Layout with 32
        Let mok_l be proc vect_decompose_value with context_ptr, loop_info, mul_left, macc_l, depth plus 1
        Let mok_r be proc vect_decompose_value with context_ptr, loop_info, mul_right, macc_r, depth plus 1
        Let mresult be 0
        If mok_l is equal to 1:
            If mok_r is equal to 1:
                Note: One side must be a pure constant (delta 0, no base)
                Let mdelta_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with macc_l, 8
                Let mdelta_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with macc_r, 8
                Let mconst_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with macc_l, 16
                Let mconst_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with macc_r, 16
                Let mbase_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with macc_l, 24
                Let mbase_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with macc_r, 24
                Let scaled_acc be 0
                Let scale be 0
                If mdelta_r is equal to 0:
                    If mbase_r is equal to 0:
                        Set scaled_acc to macc_l
                        Set scale to mconst_r
                    End If
                End If
                If scaled_acc is equal to 0:
                    If mdelta_l is equal to 0:
                        If mbase_l is equal to 0:
                            Set scaled_acc to macc_r
                            Set scale to mconst_l
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                If scaled_acc is not equal to 0:
                    Let s_base be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scaled_acc, 24
                    If s_base is equal to 0:
                        Let s_delta be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scaled_acc, 8
                        Let s_const be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with scaled_acc, 16
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 0, 1
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 8, s_delta multiplied by scale
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with acc, 16, s_const multiplied by scale
                        Set mresult to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with macc_l
        proc deallocate from Layout with macc_r
        Return mresult
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MEMORY ACCESS ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Builds one MemoryAccess record per plain LOAD (20200) / STORE (20201) in
the body. Address and byte offset come from the canonical extended-field
accessors (MIRLoad address@80 offset@88; MIRStore address@72 value@80
offset@88); the element size comes from the access type's HIRTypeInfo
size slot (offset 16, the same contract the LIR builder reads for
register widths), defaulting to 8 under the int64-everywhere ABI when
the type is absent. Volatile accesses (ext offset 104 on both shapes)
are rejected: widening coalesces and reorders the per-iteration memory
transactions, which volatile semantics forbid.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_memory_access" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, inst_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst_ptr

    Note: Volatile flag at ext offset 104 on MIRLoad and MIRStore alike
    Let is_volatile be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 104
    If is_volatile is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let mem_access be proc allocate from Layout with 72
    If mem_access is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_store be 0
    Let address_value be 0
    Let byte_offset be 0
    Let elem_type be 0
    If opcode is equal to 20200:
        Set address_value to proc get_load_address from MIRNodes with inst_ptr
        Set byte_offset to proc get_load_offset from MIRNodes with inst_ptr
        Set elem_type to proc get_load_type from MIRNodes with inst_ptr
    End If
    If opcode is equal to 20201:
        Set is_store to 1
        Set address_value to proc get_store_address from MIRNodes with inst_ptr
        Set byte_offset to proc get_store_offset from MIRNodes with inst_ptr
        Set elem_type to proc get_mir_node_type from MIR with inst_ptr
    End If

    Let element_size be 8
    If elem_type is not equal to 0:
        Let type_size be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with elem_type, 16
        If type_size is greater than 0:
            Set element_size to type_size
        End If
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with mem_access, 0, inst_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with mem_access, 8, is_store
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with mem_access, 16, address_value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with mem_access, 48, element_size

    Let acc be proc allocate from Layout with 32
    Let ok be proc vect_decompose_value with context_ptr, loop_info, address_value, acc, 0
    Let base be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with acc, 24
    Let delta be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with acc, 8
    Let const_off be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with acc, 16
    proc deallocate from Layout with acc

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with mem_access, 24, base
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with mem_access, 32, delta
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with mem_access, 40, const_off plus byte_offset
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with mem_access, 56, ok

    Let is_consecutive be 0
    If ok is equal to 1:
        If delta is equal to element_size:
            Set is_consecutive to 1
        End If
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with mem_access, 64, is_consecutive

    Return mem_access
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DEPENDENCE LEGALITY
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
The legality gate for parallel-lane execution. For every access pair
that is not load/load:

SAME BASE (identical SSA base leaf), both decomposed, equal deltas:
  diff = const_j - const_i.
  - diff == 0: the pair touches the SAME lane address every iteration.
    Lanewise widening preserves per-batch program order, so the
    dependence is satisfied inside each lane: SAFE.
  - diff a non-zero exact multiple of delta: the pair coincides d =
    diff/delta iterations apart - a loop-carried dependence: FATAL
    (reason 6). WAR/WAW are fatal too: no privatization transform
    exists in this pass, and "can privatize" without a privatizer is
    wrong-code.
  - diff NOT a multiple of delta (delta nonzero): the residues never
    coincide at any iteration pair: provably independent, SAFE.
  - deltas differ or delta 0 with diff != 0: coincidence cannot be
    excluded: FATAL (reason 6, conservative).

DIFFERENT BASES: accepted only when BOTH bases are results of DISTINCT
ALLOCA (20202) instructions - distinct stack objects cannot overlap.
Anything else (parameters, loaded pointers) is unprovable aliasing:
FATAL (reason 7). A future points-to integration can only WIDEN this
acceptance, never need to narrow it.

Every consulted pair is recorded as a DependencyInfo for reporting.
Returns 1 when the loop is dependence-safe, 0 after rejecting.
@End Reasoning

Process called "analyze_dependencies" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    Let def_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 24
    Let accesses be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 112
    Let deps be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 120

    Let access_count be proc length from List with accesses
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than access_count:
        Let access_i be proc get from List with accesses, i
        Let j be i plus 1
        While j is less than access_count:
            Let access_j be proc get from List with accesses, j

            Let store_i be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_i, 8
            Let store_j be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_j, 8
            Let either_store be store_i plus store_j
            If either_store is greater than 0:
                Note: Classify the pair: 1 RAW, 2 WAR, 3 WAW
                Let dep_type be 0
                If store_i is equal to 1:
                    If store_j is equal to 0:
                        Set dep_type to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set dep_type to 3
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    Set dep_type to 2
                End If

                Let ok_i be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_i, 56
                Let ok_j be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_j, 56
                Let base_i be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_i, 24
                Let base_j be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_j, 24
                Let delta_i be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_i, 32
                Let delta_j be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_j, 32
                Let off_i be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_i, 40
                Let off_j be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access_j, 40

                Let safe be 0
                Let is_exact be 0
                Let distance be 0

                If ok_i is equal to 1:
                    If ok_j is equal to 1:
                        If base_i is equal to base_j:
                            If delta_i is equal to delta_j:
                                Let diff be off_j minus off_i
                                If diff is equal to 0:
                                    Note: Same per-lane location: lane-local order preserved
                                    Set safe to 1
                                    Set is_exact to 1
                                Otherwise:
                                    If delta_i is not equal to 0:
                                        Let q be diff divided by delta_i
                                        Let back be q multiplied by delta_i
                                        If back is equal to diff:
                                            Note: Coincides q iterations apart: loop-carried
                                            Set distance to q
                                            Set is_exact to 1
                                        Otherwise:
                                            Note: Residues never coincide
                                            Set safe to 1
                                            Set is_exact to 1
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            Note: Different bases: provable only for distinct ALLOCAs
                            If base_i is not equal to 0:
                                If base_j is not equal to 0:
                                    Let def_i be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, base_i
                                    Let def_j be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, base_j
                                    If def_i is not equal to 0:
                                        If def_j is not equal to 0:
                                            If def_i is not equal to def_j:
                                                Let op_i be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with def_i
                                                Let op_j be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with def_j
                                                If op_i is equal to 20202:
                                                    If op_j is equal to 20202:
                                                        Set safe to 1
                                                    End If
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If

                Let dep be proc allocate from Layout with 48
                If dep is not equal to 0:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dep, 0, access_i
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dep, 8, access_j
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dep, 16, dep_type
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dep, 24, distance
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dep, 32, is_exact
                    Let blocks be 1
                    If safe is equal to 1:
                        Set blocks to 0
                    End If
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dep, 40, blocks
                    proc append from List with deps, dep
                End If

                If safe is equal to 0:
                    If base_i is equal to base_j:
                        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 6
                    Otherwise:
                        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 7
                    End If
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BODY CLASSIFICATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Partitions the loop body into the SCALAR set (the IV phi, the IV update,
the exit compare, terminators, and the backward address slice of every
memory access - address arithmetic stays scalar because vector memory
ops take a SCALAR lane-0 address) and the WIDEN set (plain consecutive
loads/stores and the lowerable arithmetic band ADD/SUB/MUL/DIV/AND/OR/
XOR). Everything else in the body is rejected (reason 5): calls,
atomics, casts, field/deref memory forms, MOD, NEG, shifts, copies, and
comparisons other than the exit test have no lowerable lanewise form in
this backend.

Cross-set dataflow rules (each violation is a distinct honest reason):
- a memory op inside an address slice (a loaded pointer feeding another
  access) makes the slice non-scalar: reason 14;
- a widened op's DATA operand defined by a scalar-set instruction, an
  out-of-loop value, or a constant would need a broadcast - the band
  has MIR_VECTOR_BROADCAST 20615 but lower_vector_op has no arm for it,
  so emitting it would produce wrong LIR: reason 11;
- a widened value consumed by any instruction OUTSIDE the widen set
  (scalar consumer of a vector register, including uses outside the
  loop) is reason 11 as well.

Also collects the memory accesses (populating loop.accesses) and
enforces consecutiveness (reason 2 / 14 for failed decompositions).

Returns an OMap (instruction pointer -> 1) of the widen set, or 0 after
rejecting. The caller owns and destroys the map.
@End Reasoning

Process called "classify_loop_body" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8
    Let def_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 24
    Let body_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 24
    Let header_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 0
    Let iv_phi be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 40
    Let iv_update be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 56
    Let exit_test_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 128
    Let accesses be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 112

    Note: Resolve the exit compare instruction (validated by trip analysis)
    Let test_block be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, exit_test_id
    Let terminator be proc get_block_terminator from CFG with test_block
    Let condition be proc get_branch_condition from MIRNodes with terminator
    Let cond_inst be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, condition

    Let widen_map be proc omap_create from OMap
    Let scalar_map be proc omap_create from OMap

    Note: ---- Pass A: bucket every body instruction
    Let mem_insts be proc create from List
    Let arith_insts be proc create from List

    Let body_list be proc to_list from Set with body_set
    Let body_count be proc length from List with body_list
    Let b be 0
    Let bucket_ok be 1
    While b is less than body_count:
        Let block_id be proc get from List with body_list, b
        Let block_ptr be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, block_id
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block_ptr
            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
                Let ii be 0
                While ii is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, ii
                    If inst is not equal to 0:
                        Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst

                        Let handled be 0
                        If inst is equal to iv_phi:
                            proc omap_set from OMap with scalar_map, inst, 1
                            Set handled to 1
                        End If
                        If inst is equal to iv_update:
                            proc omap_set from OMap with scalar_map, inst, 1
                            Set handled to 1
                        End If
                        If inst is equal to cond_inst:
                            proc omap_set from OMap with scalar_map, inst, 1
                            Set handled to 1
                        End If

                        If handled is equal to 0:
                            If opcode is equal to 20301:
                                Set handled to 1
                            End If
                            If opcode is equal to 20302:
                                Set handled to 1
                            End If
                        End If

                        If handled is equal to 0:
                            If opcode is equal to 20300:
                                Note: A phi that is not the IV (header phis were
                                Note: counted; this also covers non-header phis)
                                Set bucket_ok to 0
                                proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 12
                                Set handled to 1
                            End If
                        End If

                        If handled is equal to 0:
                            If opcode is equal to 20001:
                                Note: In-body constants stay scalar; data-side
                                Note: consumption is rejected by the operand check
                                proc omap_set from OMap with scalar_map, inst, 1
                                Set handled to 1
                            End If
                        End If

                        If handled is equal to 0:
                            If opcode is equal to 20200:
                                proc append from List with mem_insts, inst
                                Set handled to 1
                            End If
                            If opcode is equal to 20201:
                                proc append from List with mem_insts, inst
                                Set handled to 1
                            End If
                        End If

                        If handled is equal to 0:
                            Let is_widen_arith be 0
                            If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002:
                                If opcode is less than or equal to 20005:
                                    Set is_widen_arith to 1
                                End If
                            End If
                            If opcode is greater than or equal to 20010:
                                If opcode is less than or equal to 20012:
                                    Set is_widen_arith to 1
                                End If
                            End If
                            If is_widen_arith is equal to 1:
                                proc append from List with arith_insts, inst
                                Set handled to 1
                            End If
                        End If

                        If handled is equal to 0:
                            Note: Calls, atomics, casts, field/deref memory,
                            Note: MOD/NEG/shifts/copies/compares: not widenable
                            Set bucket_ok to 0
                            proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 5
                        End If
                    End If
                    If bucket_ok is equal to 0:
                        Set ii to inst_count
                    End If
                    Set ii to ii plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        If bucket_ok is equal to 0:
            Set b to body_count
        End If
        Set b to b plus 1
    End While
    proc destroy from List with body_list

    If bucket_ok is equal to 0:
        proc destroy from List with mem_insts
        proc destroy from List with arith_insts
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with widen_map
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with scalar_map
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Pass B: backward address slice (stays scalar)
    Let slice_ok be 1
    Let slice_work be proc create from List
    Let mem_count be proc length from List with mem_insts
    Let m be 0
    While m is less than mem_count:
        Let mem_inst be proc get from List with mem_insts, m
        Let mem_opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with mem_inst
        Let addr_value be 0
        If mem_opcode is equal to 20200:
            Set addr_value to proc get_load_address from MIRNodes with mem_inst
        Otherwise:
            Set addr_value to proc get_store_address from MIRNodes with mem_inst
        End If
        proc append from List with slice_work, addr_value
        Set m to m plus 1
    End While

    While proc length from List with slice_work is greater than 0:
        Let sw_len be proc length from List with slice_work
        Let slice_value be proc get from List with slice_work, sw_len minus 1
        proc remove_at from List with slice_work, sw_len minus 1

        If slice_value is not equal to 0:
            Let slice_def be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, slice_value
            If slice_def is not equal to 0:
                Let sd_block be proc get_mir_node_parent_block from MIR with slice_def
                Let sd_block_id be 0 minus 1
                If sd_block is not equal to 0:
                    Set sd_block_id to proc get_mir_basic_block_id from CFG with sd_block
                End If
                Let sd_in_body be proc contains from Set with body_set, sd_block_id
                If sd_in_body is equal to 1:
                    Let seen be proc omap_get from OMap with scalar_map, slice_def
                    If seen is equal to 0:
                        Let sd_opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with slice_def
                        Note: The IV phi and update are already scalar-marked;
                        Note: anything else in the slice must be pure arith/const
                        Let slice_member_ok be 0
                        If sd_opcode is equal to 20001:
                            Set slice_member_ok to 1
                        End If
                        If sd_opcode is greater than or equal to 20002:
                            If sd_opcode is less than or equal to 20005:
                                Set slice_member_ok to 1
                            End If
                        End If
                        If sd_opcode is greater than or equal to 20010:
                            If sd_opcode is less than or equal to 20012:
                                Set slice_member_ok to 1
                            End If
                        End If
                        If slice_member_ok is equal to 0:
                            Note: A load (or anything impure) feeding an address
                            Set slice_ok to 0
                        Otherwise:
                            proc omap_set from OMap with scalar_map, slice_def, 1
                            Let used be proc get_instruction_used_values from CFG with slice_def
                            If used is not equal to 0:
                                Let used_count be proc length from List with used
                                Let u be 0
                                While u is less than used_count:
                                    Let used_value be proc get from List with used, u
                                    proc append from List with slice_work, used_value
                                    Set u to u plus 1
                                End While
                                proc destroy from List with used
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If slice_ok is equal to 0:
            proc list_clear from List with slice_work
        End If
    End While
    proc destroy from List with slice_work

    If slice_ok is equal to 0:
        proc destroy from List with mem_insts
        proc destroy from List with arith_insts
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with widen_map
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with scalar_map
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 14
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Pass C: the widen set = mem ops + arith not claimed scalar
    Let widen_count be 0
    Set m to 0
    While m is less than mem_count:
        Let w_mem be proc get from List with mem_insts, m
        proc omap_set from OMap with widen_map, w_mem, 1
        Set widen_count to widen_count plus 1
        Set m to m plus 1
    End While
    Let arith_count be proc length from List with arith_insts
    Let a be 0
    While a is less than arith_count:
        Let w_arith be proc get from List with arith_insts, a
        Let claimed be proc omap_get from OMap with scalar_map, w_arith
        If claimed is equal to 0:
            proc omap_set from OMap with widen_map, w_arith, 1
            Set widen_count to widen_count plus 1
        End If
        Set a to a plus 1
    End While
    proc destroy from List with mem_insts
    proc destroy from List with arith_insts

    If widen_count is equal to 0:
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with widen_map
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with scalar_map
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 10
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Pass D: per-access analysis + widened operand discipline
    Let pass_d_ok be 1
    Let d_reason be 0
    Let body_list2 be proc to_list from Set with body_set
    Let body_count2 be proc length from List with body_list2
    Let b2 be 0
    While b2 is less than body_count2:
        Let block_id2 be proc get from List with body_list2, b2
        Let block_ptr2 be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, block_id2
        If block_ptr2 is not equal to 0:
            Let instructions2 be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block_ptr2
            If instructions2 is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count2 be proc length from List with instructions2
                Let i2 be 0
                While i2 is less than inst_count2:
                    Let inst2 be proc get from List with instructions2, i2
                    Let in_widen be proc omap_get from OMap with widen_map, inst2
                    If in_widen is equal to 1:
                        Let opcode2 be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst2

                        Let mem_kind be 0
                        If opcode2 is equal to 20200:
                            Set mem_kind to 1
                        End If
                        If opcode2 is equal to 20201:
                            Set mem_kind to 1
                        End If

                        If mem_kind is equal to 1:
                            Let access be proc analyze_memory_access with context_ptr, loop_info, inst2
                            If access is equal to 0:
                                Note: Volatile or allocation failure
                                Set pass_d_ok to 0
                                Set d_reason to 14
                            Otherwise:
                                proc append from List with accesses, access
                                Let decomposed be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access, 56
                                Let consecutive be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with access, 64
                                If decomposed is equal to 0:
                                    Set pass_d_ok to 0
                                    Set d_reason to 14
                                End If
                                If consecutive is equal to 0:
                                    If pass_d_ok is equal to 1:
                                        Set pass_d_ok to 0
                                        Set d_reason to 2
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If

                            Note: A store's VALUE operand must be vector-defined
                            If pass_d_ok is equal to 1:
                                If opcode2 is equal to 20201:
                                    Let store_value be proc get_store_value from MIRNodes with inst2
                                    Let sv_def be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, store_value
                                    Let sv_widen be 0
                                    If sv_def is not equal to 0:
                                        Set sv_widen to proc omap_get from OMap with widen_map, sv_def
                                    End If
                                    If sv_widen is not equal to 1:
                                        Set pass_d_ok to 0
                                        Set d_reason to 11
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            Note: Widened arithmetic: both data operands must be
                            Note: defined by widen-set members (no broadcast arm
                            Note: exists in the LIR vector lowering)
                            Let w_left be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst2, 1
                            Let w_right be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst2, 2
                            Let wl_def be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, w_left
                            Let wr_def be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, w_right
                            Let wl_ok be 0
                            Let wr_ok be 0
                            If wl_def is not equal to 0:
                                Set wl_ok to proc omap_get from OMap with widen_map, wl_def
                            End If
                            If wr_def is not equal to 0:
                                Set wr_ok to proc omap_get from OMap with widen_map, wr_def
                            End If
                            If wl_ok is not equal to 1:
                                Set pass_d_ok to 0
                                Set d_reason to 11
                            End If
                            If wr_ok is not equal to 1:
                                Set pass_d_ok to 0
                                Set d_reason to 11
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                    If pass_d_ok is equal to 0:
                        Set i2 to inst_count2
                    End If
                    Set i2 to i2 plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        If pass_d_ok is equal to 0:
            Set b2 to body_count2
        End If
        Set b2 to b2 plus 1
    End While
    proc destroy from List with body_list2

    If pass_d_ok is equal to 0:
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with widen_map
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with scalar_map
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, d_reason
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: ---- Pass E: no widened value may escape the widen set
    Let escape_ok be 1
    Let blocks be proc get_mir_cfg_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    Let all_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let e be 0
    While e is less than all_count:
        Let e_block be proc get from List with blocks, e
        If e_block is not equal to 0:
            Let e_insts be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with e_block
            If e_insts is not equal to 0:
                Let e_count be proc length from List with e_insts
                Let ei be 0
                While ei is less than e_count:
                    Let e_inst be proc get from List with e_insts, ei
                    If e_inst is not equal to 0:
                        Let e_widen be proc omap_get from OMap with widen_map, e_inst
                        If e_widen is not equal to 1:
                            Let e_used be proc get_instruction_used_values from CFG with e_inst
                            If e_used is not equal to 0:
                                Let eu_count be proc length from List with e_used
                                Let eu be 0
                                While eu is less than eu_count:
                                    Let eu_value be proc get from List with e_used, eu
                                    Let eu_def be proc omap_get from OMap with def_map, eu_value
                                    If eu_def is not equal to 0:
                                        Let eu_widen be proc omap_get from OMap with widen_map, eu_def
                                        If eu_widen is equal to 1:
                                            Set escape_ok to 0
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                    Set eu to eu plus 1
                                End While
                                proc destroy from List with e_used
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                    If escape_ok is equal to 0:
                        Set ei to e_count
                    End If
                    Set ei to ei plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        If escape_ok is equal to 0:
            Set e to all_count
        End If
        Set e to e plus 1
    End While

    proc omap_destroy from OMap with scalar_map

    If escape_ok is equal to 0:
        proc omap_destroy from OMap with widen_map
        proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 11
        Return 0
    End If

    Return widen_map
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: COST MODEL
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Fixed-point profitability estimate (scaled by 100). Inside the proven
domain the transform adds NO runtime overhead - no prologue, no
epilogue, no guards - so the model is a pure throughput ratio:

  scalar_cost = arith_widened * 1 + mem_widened * 4 + scalar_body * 1
  vector_cost = ceil(arith/VF) * 1 + ceil(mem/VF) * 4 + scalar_body * 1
  ratio       = scalar_cost * 100 / vector_cost   (>= threshold to pass)

The 4:1 memory weight reflects the L1-hit-vs-register cycle ratio; the
scalar_body term (the IV update + compare + terminator overhead per
vector iteration) is what keeps degenerate one-op loops from showing
fictitious VF-fold speedups. The classification gate already rejected
widen_count == 0, so the division is always well-defined.
@End Reasoning

Process called "compute_vectorization_cost" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, widen_map as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8
    Let body_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 24
    Let vf be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 72
    Let threshold be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 64

    Let arith_w be 0
    Let mem_w be 0
    Let scalar_ops be 0

    Let body_list be proc to_list from Set with body_set
    Let body_count be proc length from List with body_list
    Let b be 0
    While b is less than body_count:
        Let block_id be proc get from List with body_list, b
        Let block_ptr be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, block_id
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block_ptr
            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
                Let i be 0
                While i is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, i
                    If inst is not equal to 0:
                        Let in_widen be proc omap_get from OMap with widen_map, inst
                        If in_widen is equal to 1:
                            Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst
                            Let is_mem be 0
                            If opcode is equal to 20200:
                                Set is_mem to 1
                            End If
                            If opcode is equal to 20201:
                                Set is_mem to 1
                            End If
                            If is_mem is equal to 1:
                                Set mem_w to mem_w plus 1
                            Otherwise:
                                Set arith_w to arith_w plus 1
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            Set scalar_ops to scalar_ops plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set i to i plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        Set b to b plus 1
    End While
    proc destroy from List with body_list

    Let scalar_cost be arith_w plus (mem_w multiplied by 4) plus scalar_ops

    Let arith_v be (arith_w plus vf minus 1) divided by vf
    Let mem_v be (mem_w plus vf minus 1) divided by vf
    Let vector_cost be arith_v plus (mem_v multiplied by 4) plus scalar_ops
    If vector_cost is less than 1:
        Set vector_cost to 1
    End If

    Let ratio be (scalar_cost multiplied by 100) divided by vector_cost
    If ratio is less than threshold:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TRANSFORMATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Block-list surgery primitives. The canonical MIRBasicBlock layout (Part
1.1: instructions@16, instruction_count@24; MIRNode parent_block@56) has
append (add_instruction_to_block) and detach (remove_instruction_from_
block) primitives but no positional insert/replace, which the in-place
widening needs. Both helpers keep the cached count and the parent
back-pointers coherent; replace clears the detached record's
parent_block so a stale pointer can never be followed.
@End Reasoning

Process called "vect_insert_instruction_at" that takes block_ptr as Integer, index as Integer, inst_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If block_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If inst_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block_ptr
    If instructions is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc insert from List with instructions, index, inst_ptr
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block_ptr, 24
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with block_ptr, 24, count plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 56, block_ptr
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "vect_replace_instruction_at" that takes block_ptr as Integer, index as Integer, new_inst as Integer returns Integer:
    If block_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If new_inst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block_ptr
    If instructions is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old_inst be proc get from List with instructions, index
    proc set from List with instructions, index, new_inst
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_inst, 56, block_ptr
    If old_inst is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with old_inst, 56, 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
The widening transform. Every gate has passed; the rewrite is exactly
equivalent to the scalar loop:

- each widened scalar record is REPLACED by a fresh canonical
  MIRVectorOp (OD-1 prefix-embedded 128-byte record via
  MIRNodes.create_mir_vector_op - never an in-place opcode morph across
  record sizes) carrying the SAME result value id, so every existing
  use remains valid; register_value_definition re-points the function's
  value_to_instruction entry at the replacement;
- LOAD 20200 -> MIR_VECTOR_LOAD 20610 (op1 = scalar lane-0 address);
  a non-zero byte offset is folded first through a fresh CONST + scalar
  ADD (fresh ids via MIR.allocate_value_id) because the vector record
  carries no offset slot;
- STORE 20201 -> MIR_VECTOR_STORE 20611 (op1 = address, op2 = value);
- ADD/SUB/MUL/DIV 20002-20005 -> 20600-20603; AND/OR/XOR 20010-20012 ->
  20620-20622 (the exact set lower_vector_op lowers);
- the IV step constant is replaced by a freshly materialized CONST(VF)
  rewired through MIRNodes.set_mir_node_used_value (header operand and
  extended mirror stay coherent) - the ORIGINAL stride constant record
  is left untouched because other instructions may share it;
- the loop bound, test, and CFG shape are untouched: with trips an
  exact multiple of VF, stepping the same range by VF executes
  trips/VF batches covering every scalar iteration exactly once, and
  the IV's post-loop value (init + trips) is bit-identical to the
  scalar loop's, so post-loop consumers of the IV chain see no change.

Returns the number of instructions widened.
@End Reasoning

@Security_Scope
The equivalence argument above is the soundness contract: any edit that
widens outside the proven domain (unknown trip counts, non-divisible
trip counts, broadcast-needing operands, unproven aliasing) reintroduces
the wrong-code classes this rebuild removed. Extend the DOMAIN GATES,
never the transform's assumptions.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "transform_loop_to_vector" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, widen_map as Integer returns Integer:
    Let function_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 0
    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8
    Let body_set be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 24
    Let vf be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 72
    Let iv_update be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 56
    Let iv_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 48

    Let widened be 0

    Let body_list be proc to_list from Set with body_set
    Let body_count be proc length from List with body_list
    Let b be 0
    While b is less than body_count:
        Let block_id be proc get from List with body_list, b
        Let block_ptr be proc get_block_by_id_from_cfg from CFG with cfg_ptr, block_id
        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with block_ptr
            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let i be 0
                While i is less than proc length from List with instructions:
                    Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, i
                    Let in_widen be 0
                    If inst is not equal to 0:
                        Set in_widen to proc omap_get from OMap with widen_map, inst
                    End If
                    If in_widen is equal to 1:
                        Let opcode be proc get_mir_node_opcode from MIR with inst
                        Let result_id be proc get_mir_node_value_id from MIR with inst
                        Let elem_type be proc get_mir_node_type from MIR with inst

                        If opcode is equal to 20200:
                            Note: ---- LOAD -> VECTOR_LOAD
                            Let load_addr be proc get_load_address from MIRNodes with inst
                            Let load_off be proc get_load_offset from MIRNodes with inst
                            Let load_type be proc get_load_type from MIRNodes with inst
                            If load_off is not equal to 0:
                                Let off_id be proc allocate_value_id from MIR with function_ptr
                                Let off_const be proc create_mir_const from MIRNodes with off_id, load_off, load_type, 0, 0
                                proc vect_insert_instruction_at with block_ptr, i, off_const
                                proc register_value_definition from MIR with function_ptr, off_id, off_const
                                Set i to i plus 1

                                Let addr_id be proc allocate_value_id from MIR with function_ptr
                                Let addr_add be proc create_mir_binary_op from MIRNodes with 20002, addr_id, load_addr, off_id, load_type
                                proc vect_insert_instruction_at with block_ptr, i, addr_add
                                proc register_value_definition from MIR with function_ptr, addr_id, addr_add
                                Set i to i plus 1
                                Set load_addr to addr_id
                            End If
                            Let vload be proc create_mir_vector_op from MIRNodes with 20610, result_id, load_addr, 0, 0, vf, load_type, 0
                            proc vect_replace_instruction_at with block_ptr, i, vload
                            proc register_value_definition from MIR with function_ptr, result_id, vload
                            Set widened to widened plus 1
                        End If

                        If opcode is equal to 20201:
                            Note: ---- STORE -> VECTOR_STORE
                            Let store_addr be proc get_store_address from MIRNodes with inst
                            Let store_value be proc get_store_value from MIRNodes with inst
                            Let store_off be proc get_store_offset from MIRNodes with inst
                            If store_off is not equal to 0:
                                Let soff_id be proc allocate_value_id from MIR with function_ptr
                                Let soff_const be proc create_mir_const from MIRNodes with soff_id, store_off, elem_type, 0, 0
                                proc vect_insert_instruction_at with block_ptr, i, soff_const
                                proc register_value_definition from MIR with function_ptr, soff_id, soff_const
                                Set i to i plus 1

                                Let saddr_id be proc allocate_value_id from MIR with function_ptr
                                Let saddr_add be proc create_mir_binary_op from MIRNodes with 20002, saddr_id, store_addr, soff_id, elem_type
                                proc vect_insert_instruction_at with block_ptr, i, saddr_add
                                proc register_value_definition from MIR with function_ptr, saddr_id, saddr_add
                                Set i to i plus 1
                                Set store_addr to saddr_id
                            End If
                            Let vstore be proc create_mir_vector_op from MIRNodes with 20611, 0, store_addr, store_value, 0, vf, elem_type, 0
                            proc vect_replace_instruction_at with block_ptr, i, vstore
                            Set widened to widened plus 1
                        End If

                        Let vop be 0
                        If opcode is equal to 20002:
                            Set vop to 20600
                        End If
                        If opcode is equal to 20003:
                            Set vop to 20601
                        End If
                        If opcode is equal to 20004:
                            Set vop to 20602
                        End If
                        If opcode is equal to 20005:
                            Set vop to 20603
                        End If
                        If opcode is equal to 20010:
                            Set vop to 20620
                        End If
                        If opcode is equal to 20011:
                            Set vop to 20621
                        End If
                        If opcode is equal to 20012:
                            Set vop to 20622
                        End If
                        If vop is not equal to 0:
                            Let a_left be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst, 1
                            Let a_right be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with inst, 2
                            Let varith be proc create_mir_vector_op from MIRNodes with vop, result_id, a_left, a_right, 0, vf, elem_type, 0
                            proc vect_replace_instruction_at with block_ptr, i, varith
                            proc register_value_definition from MIR with function_ptr, result_id, varith
                            Set widened to widened plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set i to i plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
        Set b to b plus 1
    End While
    proc destroy from List with body_list

    Note: ---- IV step: 1 -> VF through a fresh constant
    Let upd_left be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with iv_update, 1
    Let upd_right be proc get_mir_node_operand from MIR with iv_update, 2
    Let stride_slot be 2
    If upd_right is equal to iv_value:
        Set stride_slot to 1
    End If

    Let iv_type be proc get_mir_node_type from MIR with iv_update
    Let vf_id be proc allocate_value_id from MIR with function_ptr
    Let vf_const be proc create_mir_const from MIRNodes with vf_id, vf, iv_type, 0, 0

    Note: Insert the new step constant immediately before the update
    Let upd_block be proc get_mir_node_parent_block from MIR with iv_update
    Let upd_insts be proc get_block_instructions from MIR with upd_block
    Let upd_count be proc length from List with upd_insts
    Let upd_idx be 0
    Let scan be 0
    While scan is less than upd_count:
        Let scan_inst be proc get from List with upd_insts, scan
        If scan_inst is equal to iv_update:
            Set upd_idx to scan
            Set scan to upd_count
        End If
        Set scan to scan plus 1
    End While
    proc vect_insert_instruction_at with upd_block, upd_idx, vf_const
    proc register_value_definition from MIR with function_ptr, vf_id, vf_const
    proc set_mir_node_used_value from MIRNodes with iv_update, stride_slot, vf_id

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 104, vf
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 88, 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 80, vf

    Let total be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 56
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 56, total plus widened
    Let v_loops be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 40, v_loops plus 1

    Return widened
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MAIN ENTRY POINTS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Per-function driver. Gate order is load-bearing: shape gates (innermost,
exit edge, preheader) come before the IV/trip analysis they feed;
classification populates the access list the dependence gate consumes;
the divisibility gate runs after the trip count and the vector factor
are both known; the cost gate runs last so rejected loops never pay for
transformation. Each loop is independent - one rejection never aborts
the pass - and the transform itself runs only when every gate returned
success, so a function is never left half-widened.
@End Reasoning

Process called "optimize_function_with_vectorization" that takes function_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If function_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let context_ptr be proc create_vectorization_context with function_ptr
    If context_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let loops_found be proc detect_natural_loops with context_ptr
    If loops_found is equal to 0:
        proc destroy_vectorization_context with context_ptr
        Return 1
    End If

    Let loops be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 32
    Let loop_count be proc length from List with loops
    Let vf be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 72

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than loop_count:
        Let loop_info be proc get from List with loops, i
        Let proceed be 1

        Note: Already rejected during detection (multi-latch)?
        Let prior_reason be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 96
        If prior_reason is not equal to 0:
            Set proceed to 0
        End If

        Note: ---- Innermost gate: no other loop's header inside this body
        If proceed is equal to 1:
            Let my_body be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 24
            Let my_header be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 0
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than loop_count:
                If j is not equal to i:
                    Let other be proc get from List with loops, j
                    Let other_header be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with other, 0
                    If other_header is not equal to my_header:
                        Let inside be proc contains from Set with my_body, other_header
                        If inside is equal to 1:
                            proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 15
                            Set proceed to 0
                            Set j to loop_count
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If

        If proceed is equal to 1:
            Set proceed to proc analyze_induction_variable with context_ptr, loop_info
        End If
        If proceed is equal to 1:
            Set proceed to proc analyze_trip_count with context_ptr, loop_info
        End If

        Let widen_map be 0
        If proceed is equal to 1:
            Set widen_map to proc classify_loop_body with context_ptr, loop_info
            If widen_map is equal to 0:
                Set proceed to 0
            End If
        End If

        If proceed is equal to 1:
            Set proceed to proc analyze_dependencies with context_ptr, loop_info
        End If

        Note: ---- Divisibility gate: trips >= VF and trips mod VF == 0
        If proceed is equal to 1:
            Let trips be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loop_info, 80
            If trips is less than vf:
                proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 9
                Set proceed to 0
            Otherwise:
                Let batches be trips divided by vf
                Let covered be batches multiplied by vf
                If covered is not equal to trips:
                    proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 9
                    Set proceed to 0
                End If
            End If
        End If

        If proceed is equal to 1:
            Let profitable be proc compute_vectorization_cost with context_ptr, loop_info, widen_map
            If profitable is equal to 0:
                proc vect_reject with context_ptr, loop_info, 10
                Set proceed to 0
            End If
        End If

        If proceed is equal to 1:
            proc transform_loop_to_vector with context_ptr, loop_info, widen_map
        End If

        If widen_map is not equal to 0:
            proc omap_destroy from OMap with widen_map
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc print_vectorization_stats with context_ptr
    proc destroy_vectorization_context with context_ptr
    Return 1
End Process

@Implementation
Canonical pass-level alias of the per-function entry point. Takes the
MIRFunction pointer (value-id allocation and definition registration
need the function; the CFG is derived canonically from offset 8).
@End Implementation

Process called "run_vectorization_pass" that takes function_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc optimize_function_with_vectorization with function_ptr
End Process

@Implementation
Profitability pre-filter: vectorization runs at -O3 (it is the most
analysis-heavy pass in the tier) and only on functions that actually
contain a loop. The loop probe is a back-edge scan over the canonical
successor ID lists using a locally computed-and-freed dominance tree.
@End Implementation

Process called "should_run_vectorization" that takes function_ptr as Integer, optimization_level as Integer returns Integer:
    If optimization_level is less than 3:
        Return 0
    End If
    If function_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cfg_ptr be proc get_mir_function_cfg from MIR with function_ptr
    If cfg_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dom_info be proc compute_dominance_tree from Dominance with cfg_ptr
    If dom_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let has_loop be 0
    Let blocks be proc get_mir_cfg_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    If blocks is not equal to 0:
        Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than block_count:
            Let block_ptr be proc get from List with blocks, i
            If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
                Let block_id be proc get_mir_basic_block_id from CFG with block_ptr
                Let successors be proc get_block_successors from MIR with block_ptr
                If successors is not equal to 0:
                    Let succ_count be proc length from List with successors
                    Let j be 0
                    While j is less than succ_count:
                        Let succ_id be proc get from List with successors, j
                        Let is_back be proc dominates from Dominance with dom_info, succ_id, block_id
                        If is_back is equal to 1:
                            Set has_loop to 1
                            Set j to succ_count
                        End If
                        Set j to j plus 1
                    End While
                End If
            End If
            If has_loop is equal to 1:
                Set i to block_count
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc destroy_dominance_info from Dominance with dom_info
    Return has_loop
End Process

